      "comment": "SILVERWATER KID (5) produced a fair effort on debut when sixth over 1200m at Kembla Grange in a Super Maiden. Worth following up from the low draw. HUNTER ONE (8) resumes. Disappointed on when tenth over 1300m at Kembla Grange. Back without a trial and finds a very thin Maiden. REVEILLON (6) resumes. Ran some solid minor placings when last in work and trained on the track. Sat on the speed when third over 1400m at the Sapphire Coast in a Super Maiden on February 1. Won't find this as tough and likely to play a leading role. FIELDS UNITE (7) is a filly by Unite And Conquer out of Fields Of Freedom on debut for the Lynda Bundy yard. Struggled in two trial in town last year. Worth thought at this level.",
